{{orphan |date= July 2012}}

In mathematics, the '''determinantal conjecture''' of {{harvs|txt|last=Marcus|year=1972}} and {{harvs|txt|last=de Oliveira|year=1982}} asks whether the [[determinant]] of a sum ''A''&nbsp;+&nbsp;''B'' of two ''n'' by ''n'' [[Normal matrix|normal complex matrices]] ''A'' and ''B'' lies in the [[convex hull]] of the ''n''! points Π<sub>''i''</sub> (''λ(A)''<sub>''i''</sub>&nbsp;+&nbsp;''λ(B)''<sub>σ(''i'')</sub>), where the numbers ''λ(A)''<sub>''i''</sub> and ''λ(B)''<sub>''i''</sub> are the [[eigenvalues]] of ''A'' and ''B'', and ''σ'' is an element of the symmetric group ''S''<sub>''n''</sub>.

