'''Makalero''' or '''Maklere''' is a dialect of [[Makasae language|Makasae]] spoken by 6,000 people in [[East Timor]].

==Phonology==

All the information in this section is from Huber's grammar.<ref name="huber">{{cite book|last1=Huber|first1=Juliette|title=A grammar of Makalero - A Papuan language of East Timor|date=2011|publisher=LOT Utrecht}}</ref>

===Consonants===

