{{Infobox website |name = {{Wiki favicon}} Xhosa Wikipedia |logo = Wikipedia-logo.png |screenshot = |collapsible = yes |caption = |url = {{URL|xh.wikipedia.org}} |commercial = [[Charity (practice)|Charitable]] |location = [[Miami, Florida]] |launch date = |type = [[Internet encyclopedia project]] |language = [[Xhosa language]] |registration = Optional |content license = [[Creative Commons]] [[ShareAlike]] License 3.0 |owner = [[Wikimedia Foundation]] |author = }} {{InterWiki|code=xh}} The '''Xhosa Wikipedia''' is the [[Xhosa language]] edition of [[Wikipedia]]. It has {{NUMBEROF|ARTICLES|xh|N}} articles, which as of 25 August 2018 makes it the 260th largest Wikipedia.<ref>http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/List_of_Wikipedias</ref>
The Xhosa edition of Wikipedia was started in June 2003.<ref>http://stats.wikimedia.org/EN/TablesWikipediaXH.htm</ref> Its low number of articles has led to proposals to close it in 2008<ref>[https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Proposals_for_closing_projects/Closure_of_Xhosa_Wikipedia Proposals for closing projects/Closure of Xhosa Wikipedia]</ref> and 2013<ref>[https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Proposals_for_closing_projects/Closure_of_Xhosa_Wikipedia_2 Proposals for closing projects/Closure of Xhosa Wikipedia 2]</ref> (both rejected).
As Xhosa is mutually intelligible with [[Zulu language|Zulu]], both of which are [[Nguni languages]], it is possible for articles in the [[Zulu Wikipedia|Zulu edition]] to be easily translated into Xhosa for the Xhosa Wikipedia. Similar trans-wiki efforts have been made for [[Scandinavian languages|Scandinavian-language]] editions, such as the [[Swedish Wikipedia|Swedish]], [[Norwegian Wikipedia|Norwegian]], and [[Danish Wikipedia|Danish]] through [[Wikimedia Foundation|Wikimedia]]'s ''[[meta:Skanwiki|Skanwiki]]'' collaboration tool.
